<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF-MoscowBeauty     04-13 0148</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF-Moscow Beauty,0150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Here She Comes, Moscow's First Beauty Queen</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wanted: Moscow women between the ages of 17 and 27
who know how to move and speak gracefully, play an instrument and
dance.
   In June, after a citywide contest, one of these women will be
crowned ``Moscow Beauty '88,'' the Vechernaya Moskva newspaper
reported Tuesday.
   Posters go up throughout the capital today to begin the hunt for
contestants to take part in Moscow's first beauty pageant, the
paper said.
   ``We already had the idea last year,'' the head of the leisure
center at Moscow's Gorky Park, M. Kafiyatulin, was quoted as
saying. ``But we still needed time to overcome the barriers on the
way to making it a reality.''
   The paper didn't elaborate, but said Moscow was only the fourth
city in the country, after Odessa, Vilnius and Leningrad, to hold a
beauty contest.
</TEXT>
