<HEAD>Tipper Gore: We Kissed on First Date</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tipper Gore, wife of Democratic
presidential hopeful Albert Gore Jr., said that the two kissed on
their first date when she was 16 and he was 17.
   ``Absolutely!'' declared the Tennessee senator's wife when asked
Tuesday, during an interview with WVOX-WRTN radio, whether she and
her husband-to-be kissed their first time out together.
   Is he a good kisser?
   ``Well, take a look at our family and draw your own
conclusion,'' the mother of four said from her Washington home.
   Tipper Gore may be best known for her campaign against obscene
and violent lyrics in rock music. She is co-founder of the Parents'
Music Resource Center and author of ``Raising PG kids in an X-Rated
Society.''
   Mrs. Gore said she met her future husband at his high school
graduation party 23 years ago. ``We both had dates with different
people,'' she said. ``He called me the next day and we made a date
for the following weekend and we've been together ever since.''
   The two were married five years later, in 1970, after she
graduated from Boston University and he from Harvard.
