<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``I believe I have been fair, firm and honest, and I have done
my best. Through a decade of quiet labor I have led my party from
the ambivalence of the Carter years through the extremes of the
Reagan administration.'' _ Sen. Robert C. Byrd, D-W.Va., announcing
his decision not to seek another term as Senate majority leader.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``Deportation is one of the means of punishment we use to deter
those who violate law and order. When there will be need in that we
will use it.'' _ Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhak Shamir, responding
to U.S. criticism of Israel's deportation of eight Palestinians to
Lebanon amid anti-Israeli riots.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``I'll help you file your tax return if you don't do this.'' _
Internal Revenue Service assistant division chief Debbie Moore, to
a taxpayer trying to dunk her in a tank of water by hitting a
target with baseballs during ``Tax Bash'' festivities in
Indianapolis. Moore got dunked.
</TEXT>
