<HEAD>Woman Shot Retarded Son in `Act of Love'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Geraldine M. Sagel, who shot her 52-year-old
retarded son because of concern about his care after her death,
died last month, according to a family member.
   Mrs. Sagel, 81, died March 29 in Condell Memorial Hospital in
Libertyville, said her daughter, Bonnie Virnala.
   In February, Mrs. Sagel pleaded guilty to aggravated battery
after shooting her son in a case a judge characterized as a
mother's misguided act of love.
   On Sept. 30 Mrs. Sagel used a .22 caliber pistol that belonged
to her husband to fire a shot at her son Jack, who was hit in the
shoulder.
