<HEAD>Anarchic Group Attacks Jewish Bookstore</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TURIN, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bookstore specializing in scientific and
Jewish publications was heavily damaged in a firebomb attack
Wednesday, police reported.
   The Luxemburg bookstore in downtown Turin had not yet opened for
the day, and no one was injured, police said.
   ``Long live the Palestinian people,'' a woman said in a call to
a local newspaper. She claimed the attack in the name of the
``Revolutionary Anarchic Group,'' a previously unknown organization.
   Police said the shop owner, Angelo Pezzana, had received several
threats in the past few weeks as left-wing extremists mounted an
anti-Israeli campaign following the four months of unrest in the
occupied West Bank and Gaza Strip.
   About a month ago a group of extremists had prevented customers
from entering the bookstore and had painted insulting slogans on
the windows.
</TEXT>
