<DOCNO> AP880413-0156 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-04-13-88 1453EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a AM-ThousandBurglaries     04-13 0344</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Thousand Burglaries,0352</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Talkative Burglar Has Police Hopping To Check Out Massive
Confessions</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An admitted burglar is keeping
lawmen from 17 police departments hopping with tales of how he
broke into more than 1,000 homes in the past two years.
   Timothy Thompson claims more than 4,000 victims in Palm Beach
County, police said, and can give minute details of the break-ins.
   ``His mind is like a computer,'' said Lantana police Sgt. Jim
Upton. ``He can tell us how he got in the house and what he took.
And we research the reports and those items are listed on the
report.''
   The Palm Beach sheriff's office Tuesday blamed Thompson for 517
burglaries in their area, and 16 cities have accused Thompson or
say he is a suspect in 552 more burglaries.
   ``This guy remembers the house, the layout of the house and what
he took,'' sheriff's Sgt. Ken Deischer said. ``He has amazing
recall.''
   Acting on a tip, Lantana police last month arrested Thompson at
the Knight's Inn on March 10. In his room, officials found stolen
clothes, handguns and jewelry, Upton said. Sheriff's detectives
later found discovered thousands of dollars in stolen merchandise
in a rented storage room near Lake Worth.
   ``We had been having a lot of residential burglaries near the
Knight's Inn,'' Upton said. ``We were getting clobbered. He was one
of the persons I had as a suspect.''
   So far, officials have recovered more than $60,000 worth of
stolen merchandise, from cowboy boots to silverware. Thompson
remains in the Palm Beach County jail on charges including
burglary, grand theft and possession of a firearm by a convicted
felon.
   Thomspon is suspected of 109 burglaries in Lantana, 35 in
Boynton Beach, 215 in Lake Worth and numerous others in Boca Raton,
Delray Beach, West Palm Beach, Manalapan, Jupiter Inlet Colony,
Palm Beach Gardens, Gulf Stream, Greenacres City, Palm Beach, Lake
Park, Jupiter, Tequesta and North Palm Beach.
   Thompson has a long history of burglary in Palm Beach County and
has served prison time, authorities said.
</TEXT>
