new supply of weapons there.
   One freed passenger who holds U.S. and Egyptian citizenship said
he hid his American passport from the gunmen, and another said they
had booby-trapped the Boeing 747's doors with explosives.
   The passengers were among 12 Arabs freed by the hijackers
Tuesday before the plane took off from Larnaca for Algiers.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Massachusetts Gov. Michael Dukakis holds a
2-to-1 lead over Jesse Jackson in ``super delegates'' who have
lined up behind a Democratic presidential contender, and that
33-vote edge among party leaders represents almost all of the
distance between the two candidates.
   Dukakis, who has the overall lead in Democratic National
Convention delegates, gained 15 super delegates over the last
month, bringing his total from that group to 63.5, according to a
survey by The Associated Press. Including delegates won in
primaries and caucuses so far, Dukakis has a total of 754.15.
   Jackson has 715.1 delegates overall, including 30.1 super
delegates, a gain of 11 over the last month.
