<1ST_LINE>r f PM-TreasuryAuction     04-13 0099</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Treasury Auction,0104</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Yields Fall on Seven-Year Notes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on seven-year Treasury notes fell in
the government's latest auction to the lowest level since last June.
   The average yield was 8.44 percent on Tuesday, down from 8.67
percent at the last comparable auction on Jan. 6.
   It was the lowest rate since seven-year notes averaged 8.10
percent on June 25. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of
8] percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,966.20.
   A total of $6.26 billion in notes were sold out of bids
totalling $16.45 billion.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
