73.87 cents per pound; feeder cattle were .62 cent lower to .05
cent higher with April at 79.60 cents per pound; hogs were .02 cent
to .50 cent lower with April at 45.15 cents per pound; frozen pork
bellies were .57 cent lower to .25 cent higher with May at 52.45
cents per pound.
   Livestock and meat futures closed sharply lower Tuesday.
