<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Earns-GeorgiaPacific     04-13 0190</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Earns-Georgia Pacific,0199</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Georgia-Pacific Earnings Up 33 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Georgia-Pacific Corp. reported Wednesday its
earnings increased 33 percent during the first quarter of 1988
although operating profits fell in the company's building products
segment.
   The company reported earnings of $106 million, or $1.02 per
share, compared with $80 million, or 71 cents a share, for the same
quarter last year.
   Sales for the quarter totaled $2.1 billion, up from $1.9 billion
in the first quarter of 1987.
   The company's building products operating profits declined to
$108 million from $119 million a year ago.
   Chairman and Chief Executive Officer T. Marshall Hahn Jr.
attributed the decline to the effect of bad weather on housing
starts and a reduced demand for gypsum products.
   However, good demand from home improvement and industrial
markets lessened the impact of the drop in housing starts.
   ``Net income was a record for the three-month period, and sales
were strong throughout the quarter,'' Hahn said. ``We are
particularly pleased with our good performance during a season when
activity is typically slower.''
   Georgia Pacific said it had good demand for its paper products
during the quarter.
</TEXT>
