<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Gillette     04-13 0309</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Gillette,0322</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gillette Reports 37 Percent Increase In Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gillette Co., under pressure from an investment
group, Wednesday credited streamlined global operations and a jump
in sales of some products for a 37 percent increase in
first-quarter earnings.
   Gillette management has been urging the company's nearly 27,000
shareholders to reject an attempt by New York-based Coniston
Partners to oust four Gillette directors at the April 21 annual
meeting in Andover.
   For the three months ended March 31, Gillette reported earnings
of $75.3 million, or 65 cents a share, on sales of $903.1 million,
compared with earnings of $55 million, or 48 cents a share, on
sales of $762.1 million for the same period last year.
   Pre-tax income from operations for the first quarter rose 30
percent to $124.9 million, compared with $96 million for the same
period in 1987.
   Razor blades, personal care items and Braun electric shavers all
sold well in the latest quarter, said Gillette spokesman David
Fausch.
   Colman M. Mockler Jr., Gillette's chairman and chief executive,
predicted 1988 earnings will increase at least 25 percent to about
$2.50 a share, compared with $2 a share for 1987 and $1.42 per
share in 1986.
   Gillette spent nearly $225 million restructuring in 1986 after
thwarting a third hostile takeover bid by Revlon Group Inc., which
agreed not to seek to gain control of Gillette under a 10-year pact
signed in November 1986. Following the accord, Gillette laid off
2,400 workers and sold off several unprofitable divisions.
   The two Coniston partnerships have accumulated 6.76 million
Gillette shares, or about 5.8 percent of the company's shares
outstanding.
   In several reports mailed to shareholders since March, Mockler
claimed Coniston plans to sell or dismember the company.
   A hostile takeover attempt by Coniston forced a major
restructuring of Allegis Corp. last year.
   Gillette has about 30,000 employees worldwide.
</TEXT>
