<TEXT>
   Bank of New York Co. said Wednesday that it has
extended by nearly a week its $1.08 billion hostile tender offer
for rival Irving Bank Corp.
   The bid _ of $15 in cash and 1.575 shares of Bank of New York
stock for each of Irving's roughly 18.1 million common shares
outstanding _ is now set to expire at 2 p.m. EDT April 21. That's
the day Irving's shareholders are expected to vote on the poposal.
